'''MiniDLNA''' (also known as ReadyMedia) is [[Article description::a media server aiming to be DLNA/UPnP-AV compliant.]]

== Installation ==

=== USE flags ===

{{USEflag|package=net-misc/minidlna}}

=== Emerge ===

Install {{Package|net-misc/minidlna}}:

{{Emerge|net-misc/minidlna}}

== Configuration ==

Configuration is controlled by {{Path|/etc/minidlna.conf}} these settings should be changed.

{{FileBox|filename=/etc/minidlna.conf|1=
#friendly_name=My DLNA Server
media_dir=/opt
}}

=== Automatic file discovery ===

MiniDLNA supports [[Wikipedia:Inotify|inotify]] monitoring to automatically discover new files. To enable inotify support the kernel needs to have inotify support enabled.

{{KernelBox|title=Enabling inotify support|1=<nowiki />
    File systems --->
      [*] Inotify support for userspace
}}

And <code>inotify=yes</code> set in the MiniDLNA configuration file.

{{FileBox|filename=/etc/minidlna.conf|1=
inotify=yes
}}

=== Manual database rebuild ===

{{RootCmd|rc-service minidlna stop && minidlnad -R}}

=== Port forwarding ===

MiniDLNA uses UDP port 1900 & TCP port 8200.

=== Service ===

==== OpenRC ====

Start MiniDLNA:

{{RootCmd|rc-service minidlna start}}

Start MiniDLNA at boot:

{{RootCmd|rc-update add minidlna default}}

==== systemd ====

Start MiniDLNA:

{{RootCmd|systemctl start minidlna}}

Start MiniDLNA at boot:

{{RootCmd|systemctl enable minidlna}}

